From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Infinity Kernel <infinity@kernel.dev>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 05/10] tcp: enable BBR congestion control and Fast Open by default

Enable TCP BBR, Westwood, and HTCP congestion control algorithms
for SM7325 (vayu/bhima). BBR is selected with FQ_CODEL queuing
discipline for optimal throughput. TCP Fast Open default changed
from 1 (client-only) to 3 (client+server) to reduce connection
latency on both sides. TFO SYN data payload limit increased for
more efficient first-packet data delivery.

Signed-off-by: Infinity Kernel <infinity@kernel.dev>
---
 net/ipv4/Kconfig      | 12 ++++++++++++
 net/ipv4/Makefile     |  1 +
 net/ipv4/tcp_ipv4.c   |  2 +-
 net/ipv4/tcp_output.c |  4 +++-
 4 files changed, 17 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/ipv4/Kconfig b/net/ipv4/Kconfig
--- a/net/ipv4/Kconfig
+++ b/net/ipv4/Kconfig
@@ -253,6 +253,18 @@ config TCP_CONG_HYBLA
 	default n
 	---help---
 
+config TCP_CONG_BBR
+	tristate "BBR TCP"
+	default n
+	select NET_SCH_FQ_CODEL
+	---help---
+	  BBR (Bottleneck Bandwidth and RTT) is a model-based congestion
+	  control algorithm. BBR uses a model of the network path to estimate
+	  bottleneck bandwidth and RTT, and operates based on these estimates
+	  rather than loss-based signals. BBR requires the FQ or FQ_CODEL
+	  qdisc for proper operation. Selecting this option will automatically
+	  enable FQ_CODEL.
+
 config TCP_CONG_HTCP
 	tristate "TCP-HTCP"
 	default n
diff --git a/net/ipv4/Makefile b/net/ipv4/Makefile
--- a/net/ipv4/Makefile
+++ b/net/ipv4/Makefile
@@ -44,6 +44,7 @@ obj-$(CONFIG_INET_TCP_DIAG) += tcp_diag.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_TCP_CONG_BIC) += tcp_bic.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_TCP_CONG_CUBIC) += tcp_cubic.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_TCP_CONG_WESTWOOD) += tcp_westwood.o
+obj-$(CONFIG_TCP_CONG_BBR) += bbr.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_TCP_CONG_VEGAS) += tcp_vegas.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_INET_XFRM_TUNNEL) += xfrm4_tunnel.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_NETLINK_MMAP) += netlink_mmap.o
diff --git a/net/ipv4/tcp_ipv4.c b/net/ipv4/tcp_ipv4.c
--- a/net/ipv4/tcp_ipv4.c
+++ b/net/ipv4/tcp_ipv4.c
@@ -89,7 +89,7 @@
 int sysctl_tcp_tw_reuse __read_mostly = 0;
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(sysctl_tcp_tw_reuse);
 
-int sysctl_tcp_fastopen __read_mostly = 1;
+int sysctl_tcp_fastopen __read_mostly = 3;
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(sysctl_tcp_fastopen);
 
 int sysctl_tcp_fastopen_blackhole_timeout __read_mostly = 60;
diff --git a/net/ipv4/tcp_output.c b/net/ipv4/tcp_output.c
--- a/net/ipv4/tcp_output.c
+++ b/net/ipv4/tcp_output.c
@@ -3195,7 +3195,10 @@ static int tcp_send_syn_data(struct sock *sk, struct sk_buff *syn)
 	if (!fo || !fo->data)
 		return 0;
 
-	space = min_t(int, space, MAX_SYN_DATA_SIZE);
+	/* Increase TFO SYN payload limit to 2x for improved
+	 * fast-open efficiency on SM7325 (vayu/bhima).
+	 */
+	space = min_t(int, space, MAX_SYN_DATA_SIZE * 2);
 
 	data = fo->data;
 	iov_iter_init(&msg.msg_iter, WRITE | ITER_KVEC,
